Introduction

Shin Yuna is a South Korean dancer, rapper, singer-songwriter, and composer under JYP Entertainment. She is best known as the maknae, lead rapper, one of the lead dancers, and the visual of the girl group ITZY.

In 2016, Yuna attended a music festival together with her sister. There, she was scouted by an agent from JYP Entertainment who asked if she would be interested to audition for the company. After passing the audition, she went on to train for three years. In 2019, Yuna was revealed to be one of the members of JYP's upcoming girl group ITZY. She eventually made her official debut on February 12, 2019.
